
'''* Book: Adrian Mackenzie. Wirelessness  - Radical Empiricism in Network Cultures (2010).'''


=Description=

MacKenzie:

""The key claim of the book is that the contemporary proliferation of wireless devices and modes of network connection can best be screened against the backdrop of a broadly diverting and converging set of tendencies that I call 'wirelessness'. Wireless designates an experience trending toward entanglements with things, objects, gadgets, infrastructures, and services, and imbued with indistinct sensations and practices of network-associated changed. Wirelessness affects how people arrive, depart, and inhabit places, how they relate to others, and indeed how they embody change."
(http://machinology.blogspot.com/2011/01/wirelessness-radical-empiricism-in.html)


